Amendment No. 3 to SB0350
Akbari
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 350* House Bill No. 469
by deleting "A landlord shall not prohibit" from subsection (a) in Section 1 and substituting
"Except as provided in subsection (f), a landlord shall not prohibit".
AND FURTHER AMEND by inserting at the end of Section 1 the following as a new subsection:
(f) A landlord may:
(1) Restrict the possession, carry, or transport of a firearm, any part of a
firearm, or firearm ammunition on property described in subdivision (a)(3) to the
purpose of accessing the tenant's home, apartment, business, or other leased
premises or the tenant's or tenant's guest's vehicle located on the leased
premises or in a parking area provided by the landlord for tenants or tenant's
guests; and
(2) Require that a possessed, carried, or transported firearm be
concealed from view.
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting "A landlord shall not prohibit" from subsection (a) in
Section 2 and substituting "Except as provided in subsection (f), a landlord shall not prohibit".
AND FURTHER AMEND by inserting at the end of Section 2 the following as a new subsection:
(f) A landlord may:
(1) Restrict the possession, carry, or transport of a firearm, any part of a
firearm, or firearm ammunition on property described in subdivision (a)(3) to the
purpose of accessing the tenant's dwelling unit or premises or the tenant's or
tenant's guest's vehicle located on the leased premises or in a parking area
provided by the landlord for tenants or tenant's guests; and
